  <a href="#0" id="0">
   We investigate recognizing implied predicate-argument relationships which are not explicitly expressed in syntactic structure.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   While prior works addressed such relationships as an extension to semantic role labeling, our work investigates them in the context of textual inference scenarios.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Such scenarios provide prior information, which substantially eases the task.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   We provide a large and freely available evaluation dataset for our task setting, and propose methods to cope with it, while obtaining promising results in empirical evaluations.
  </a>
